In addition to the Basic Requirements for this position, your resume must also demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS-13 grade level or pay band in the Federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector performing the following duties:
1) Applying advanced information technology principles, methods and practices throughout the domain to secure operational cyber environments;
2) Implementing defined reporting and promulgated mitigation procedures required for commands to achieve compliance with regulations in a timely manner;
3) Assessing current information assurance/cyber security vulnerabilities and the impact of these vulnerabilities to determine associated mitigation strategies;
4) Using budget, manning, and programming requirements for information systems security measures and technologies to prepare estimates and determine resource requirements;
5) Managing Certification & Accreditation and Cyber Security operations utilizing Risk Management Framework (RMF) Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management website:
